description: We all know that the Corvette name carries a special place in car world for so many and has been the model of cutting edge design for the automotive industry for decades. And arguably the C-3 design when it came out was truly was ahead of its time with its radically shaped fenders, front end and gill-like front fenders that resembled a Mako Shark. Also new was the completely re-designed interior that featured a multiple gauge cluster in the center and large round dials in front of the driver for the speedometer and matching tachometer. And another first was a fiber-optic system that monitored exterior lights.

GR Auto Gallery is pleased to present this unmolested example of the 1971 Chevrolet Corvette LT-1 for your consideration. This vehicle has only had one single owner its entire life, hosts what is believed to be the original powertrain, has not had any major repairs to the body and has been maintained exceptionally well since new! There are so few of these that have not been “souped up” or altered in major ways which makes this a real rarity and perfect for the purists or collectors. From the factory this came with the 4-Speed close ratio manual transmission, AM/FM radio, tilt and telescopic steering wheel, t-tops, heater, power steering, power windows and power brakes. Along with the vehicle, the owner has kept wonderful records of normal service and also extra manuals and paperwork, including the original Protect-O-Plate. More often than not these vehicles end up giving way to age and finding one that has had this amount of work completed to them is a real testament to the popularity of the “Mako Shark” design. This one is as real as it gets and has all the right pieces! Call or email us today with any questions you may have on this wonderful unmolested example of the 1971 Chevrolet Corvette LT-1!

description: GR Auto Gallery is pleased to present this 1974 Chevrolet Corvette for purchase. The C3 generation of Corvettes ran from 1968 to 1982, but had some various changes throughout the run of the Stingray. With gov't restrictions killing off muscle cars the stingray had to transition to more of a cruiser. A Chevrolet advertisement headlined: "We gave it radials, a quieter ride, guard beams and a nose job." Improvements to body mounts and interior did improve the Corvette's ride and interior noise was reduced by 40%. Today, C3 Corvettes are some of the best buys in the classic automobile world. These cars were incredibly popular and provide a great ride with plenty of available spare parts. Get behind the wheel and have some classic fun in a Stingray!

GR Auto Gallery is pleased to present this 1974 Chevrolet Corvette for consideration. Coming to you in the original color of Dark Green Metallic, this Vette shows very well and sure does shine after receiving a full exterior and interior detailing. Powered by the always reliable 350 cubic inch V8 and paired with a 4-speed manual transmission. According to our vehicle intake inspection; all of the vehicles glass, wheels, lights (headlights high and low, taillights, turn signals), wipers, heater, horn, seat function, radio, windows and door locks are in good condition and all functioning as they should. With spare parts inexpensive and readily available, C3 Corvettes are a steal as far as classic cars go that can provide such a fun driving experience while turning heads down the road. Don't miss your opportunity to own this affordable American muscle car. A great find for those who love the 70's era Corvette and enjoy a uniquely beautiful ride to enjoy, call us with any questions you may have while it's still here!

description: The C3 corvette marks a Muscle car that almost anyone can recognize due to its iconic looks, drivability and performance.  This 1973 stingray fits the bill of all of these.  Equipped with dual exhaust exhaling through the popular side pipes, the L82 engine sounds great.  The differences between the L-82 and the L-48 are internal.  The L-82 was the high performance engine of its day.  It was a 4 bolt main block that had a performance cam, larger valves for the heads vs the L-48 that was a 2 bolt main and had smaller valves and milder cam.  The 350 v8 is tied to a 4 speed manual transmission with a posi-traction rear end.   The engine has an aluminum intake

The Corvette is dressed in blue over a blue vinyl interior.  The seats and interior have been redone at some point and show well.  The car comes with a car cover, AM/FM/cassette player.  It has T tops and a custom removable rear window.  The Corvette has an adjustable rear spring, upgraded trailing arms and radius arms. The C-3 Corvettes have started to see an increase in collectability and value, so this would be a good time to get your hands on one before they are out of reach.
